# Aqua Avalon — powers /api/transcribe (high-accuracy voice dictation)
# Get a key at https://app.aquavoice.com/api-dashboard
# Billing: $0.39/hour of audio; the app hard-stops itself at $9.00/month.
AQUA_API_KEY=
# Only set if Aqua's docs show a different base URL than the default:
# AQUA_BASE_URL=https://api.aquavoice.com/api/v1

# --- Book Brain AI hub (premium) ---
# Anthropic API key — powers quiz generation and (later) questions across your
# notes. Get one at https://console.anthropic.com/. Spend is capped in-app at
# $10/month across ALL accounts, with a hard stop at $9.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Who holds the premium AI capabilities, as a comma-separated list of Firebase
# uids. Unlike AQUA_ALLOWED_UIDS below, leaving this BLANK grants nobody
# anything — a paid gate on a shared budget must fail closed.
AI_ADMIN_UIDS=
# Same list again, readable by the browser. Used only to hide UI; the server
# variable above is what actually protects spend.
NEXT_PUBLIC_AI_ADMIN_UIDS=

# Service account for the shared AI spend counter. The counter is a global
# Firestore document (`aiUsage/{YYYY-MM}`) that clients must NOT be able to
# write — otherwise any signed-in account could reset everyone's budget — so
# the server needs its own credentials to read and increment it.
# Create at: Firebase console -> Project settings -> Service accounts ->
# "Generate new private key". Paste client_email here and private_key below
# with its newlines escaped as \n.
FIREBASE_SA_CLIENT_EMAIL=
FIREBASE_SA_PRIVATE_KEY=

# --- Aqua voice dictation ---
# Who may spend Aqua credit, as a comma-separated list of Firebase uids.
# /api/transcribe always requires a valid Firebase ID token, but Google
# sign-in accepts ANY Google account — so LEAVING THIS BLANK means anyone
# who signs in can bill audio to your key. Set it to your own uid — find it in
# the Firebase console under Authentication → Users → "User UID".
AQUA_ALLOWED_UIDS=
